<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-82-1269 </DOCNO><TEXT>If in the case of bottom-hinged sash windows the lateral reveal facesand the bottom side of the lintel are lined with sound-absorbing materials,we will have, even with windows open to 1 to 2 cm, an estimated soundreduction index R/sub w/' = 20 to 25 dB as a function of the chosen soundabsorption coefficient. In simple cases, the sound-absorbing reveal liningis thus a satisfactory compromise between the requirement of a soundinsulation and the need for ventilation, if no additional ventilationsystem can be installed.</TEXT></DOC>